      <header>
          <h1>Chicken biryani GFP</h1>
          <img src="biryani.jpg" alt="Chicken Biryani" class="recipe-img">
      </header>
      <section class="ingredients">
          <h2>Ingredients</h2>
          <ul>
              <li>2 cups basmati rice cooked</li>
              <li>1 kg chicken cut and marinated with spices for atleast 30mins</li>
              <li>green chillies slit 4</li>
              <li>3 medium size onions</li>
              <li>whole biryani spices </li>
              <li>ginger garlic paste</li>
              <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
              <li>1 teaspoon chilli powder</li>
              <li>1 teaspoon turmeric</li>
              <li>Â½ cup vegetable oil</li>
              <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
              <li>1 teaspoon chicken masala</li>
              <li>handfull of coriander leaves and mint leaves</li>
              <!-- More ingredients -->
          </ul>
      </section>
      <section class="instructions">
          <h2>Instructions</h2>
          <ol>
              <li>On the gas, place a wide pan.Add oil along with biryani spices and onions.Allow onions to cook on high flame till they turn brown.</li>
              <li>Then lower the flame and add the marinated chicken with 1glass of water and stir for a minute.Then let the chicken cook for about 10 - 15 minutes on medium flame(you can add any spices if neccessary at this stage).</li>
              <li>Once the chicken is cooked for 80% add chillies,coriander and mint.</li>
              <li>Add the cooked basmati rice as layers above the prepared chicken mixture.</li>
              <li>after layering, on top of rice spread some brown onions, coriander, mint and ghee for flavours.Cover the pan with lid.</li>
              <li>Place the wide pan on preheated pan.Let it sit for 5 minutes while the gas is off.</li>
              <li>After sometime serve it hot with raita along side.</li>
              <!-- More steps -->
          </ol>
      </section>
